SIMPLE: rede
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rede
<hw>Rede</hw> <pr>(r?d)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Read</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To advise or counsel.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>rede</qex> that our host here shall begin.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To interpret; to explain.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My sweven [dream] <qex>rede</qex> aright.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rede</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rede
<hw>Rede</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Read</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Advice; counsel; suggestion.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Burns.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There was none other remedy ne <qex>reed</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A word or phrase; a motto; a proverb; a wise
saw.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧This <xex>rede</xex> is
rife.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redeem</ent>⟦br⟧
